item.title: Food Instructions
item.dc:creator: Enverd Liem
item.content:encoded:
Seafood Fried Rice

Prepare :
  • Spice Guru Seafood Fried Rice Seasonings
  • 1 Bowl of Rice
  • 2 Eggs
  • 50 gram of prawn
  • Sausages
  • Onion Leaves
  • 3 Spoons of cooking oil
Instructions :
  • Add 3 spoons of cooking oil to the fry pan.
  • Put down the eggs, prawn, sausages, and onion leaves to the fry pan.
  • Mix gently until the egg is cooked.
  • Pour in the rice to the pan.
  • Use the Spice Guru Seafood Fried Rice Seasonings.
  • Stirtill the seasoning mix well with the rice.
  • Fried rice ready to be served!

Sweet and Sour Fish

Prepare :
  • Spice Guru Sweet and Sour Fish Seasoning
  • 1 whole fish, about 400g
  • 4 tablespoons tomato sauce
  • 1 teaspoon preserved soy bean paste (tau cheo)
  • 100ml water
  • 1/2 teaspoon cornstarch, mix with 2 tablespoons of water
  • 1 tablespoon light soy sauce
Instruction :
  • Boil the water.
  • Put Spice Guru Sweet and Sour Fish Seasoning to the fry pan.
  • Put 1 teaspoon preserved soy bean paste
  • Pour in the light soy sauce
  • Mix with 4 tablespoons of tomato sauce
  • Put the whole fish into the boiling water
  • Cook around 20 minutes until the fish is cooked
  • Mix the 1/2 teaspoon cornstarch with 2 tablespoon of water
  • Pour the cornstarch mixture into the soup.
  • Mix and stir quickly until the soup is thicken.
  • Sweet & Sour Fish ready to be served

Traditional Indonesian Fried Rice

Prepare:
  • Spice Guru Traditional Indonesian Fried Rice Seasonings
  • 1 Egg
  • 1 Bowl of Rice
  • Cabbage (Sufficiently)
  • Beansprout (Sufficiently)
  • Salted Anchovy
  • Cooked Shredded chicken (Sufficiently)
  • Onion Leaves
  • 3 Spoons of cooking oil
Instructions :
  • Put down 3 spoons of cooking oil into the fry pan
  • Put down the eggs, shredded chicken,anchovy and onion leavesto the fry pan.
  • Mix gently until the egg is cooked.
  • Pour in the rice to the pan.
  • Slice the Cabbage and pour it into the frying pan
  • Pour in the beansprout
  • Use theTraditional IndonesianFried Rice Seasonings.
  • Stirtill the seasoning mix well with the rice.
  • Fried rice ready to be served!
